<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:274.97px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">collected in the milk bag.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:304.13px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">However, there are a few things that our experts did not like about the product. The first thing is</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:318.65px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">the price. While the product is convenient to use and portable, the price range is not suitable for</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:333.17px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">potential customers on a shoestring budget. Nevertheless, if you have a flexible spending</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:347.69px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">account (FSA) or health spending account (HSA), you can purchase the breast pump without</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:362.21px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">hurting your pocket. You can also apply for reimbursement </span><A HREF="https://thebabyswag.com/how-to-get-a-breast-pump-through-insurance/">through your insurance</A> </span><span class="cls_002"> if it covers</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:376.85px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">breast pumps.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:405.89px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Another not-so-great thing about the product is that the reusable container is not included in the</span></div>
